Install all at once:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

**Additional requirements:**
- [Blender 4.x](https://www.blender.org/download/) — for render time benchmarking (free)
- Python 3.10+ recommended

---

## Limitations

- Render time labels are **machine-specific** — predictions are valid only for the hardware used during benchmarking
- Blender Cycles CPU rendering is used for consistency; GPU rendering would produce different (faster) times
- Dataset size is limited by available assets and render time — larger datasets improve model accuracy
- `.rar` and `.zip` compressed assets must be manually extracted before processing

---

## Future Work

- Extend to GPU render time prediction with hardware spec features
- Add Unreal Engine 5 FPS benchmarking for real-time performance prediction
- Generalize across machines by normalizing render time against a hardware benchmark score
- Graph Neural Network branch for structural mesh topology analysis
- Web-based dashboard for drag-and-drop asset analysis

